# Finding Content with Copilot
# Shows how Copilot can help users find specific documents and list items
# without knowing where things are stored.

[section: setup]

Verify the site is accessible and that the document libraries contain content
before running the demo. The Contracts and Legal Operations libraries should
have at least a few documents.

[navigate: https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]

[open-chat]

[prompt: What documents do we have about legal operations?]

[wait]

Confirm that Copilot returns at least one document result. If no results appear,
check that the Legal Operations library has content before proceeding.

[pause]

[section: demo]

[navigate: https://microsoft.sharepoint-df.com/teams/ZachDemos/]

One of the most common pain points in SharePoint: people can't find content.
They know it exists — they just don't know which library, which folder, or
what it's called. Copilot changes this.

[pause]

[open-chat]

Instead of searching manually, let's just ask.

[prompt: What documents do we have about legal operations?]

[wait]

Copilot found documents related to legal operations and can tell you where
they live. This works across libraries — the user doesn't need to know the
folder structure.

[pause]

Now let's try something more specific — asking Copilot to find a particular
type of content across the site.

[prompt: Are there any contacts or people directories on this site?]

[wait]

Notice that Copilot can reason about list types, not just document content.
It understands the difference between a contacts list and a document library.

[pause]

Let's do one more — asking about something time-sensitive. This shows
Copilot reasoning about the site as a knowledge base.

[prompt: What's the most recently updated content on this site?]

[wait]

Copilot can reference recency. This is useful for team leads who want to
quickly see what's changed, or for anyone joining a project mid-stream.

[screenshot: tools/screenshots/find-content.png]

[section: reset]

This demo is read-only — no content was created or modified.
Navigate back to the home page to reset.

